# StringHashMap
A StringHashMap is a key/value datatype in zig.
The key is a string, and the value can be any type; i.e., StringHashMap(T).

One of the most important thing to remember, is that the keys are not stored by the StringHashMap.
Instead, keys are pointers to slices that were provided when adding the key/value pair.

What does this mean?  
Because StringHashMap does not copy the keys, if the array that holds the underlying string is dereferenced, the key becomes garbage.

If the values are also strings, consider using a BufMap.  
A BufMap is what std.process.Init.envion_map uses, and apparently is built on top of StringHashMap.


